"{\"uid\": \"si.com-tennis-german-tennis-star-angelique-kerber-bids-adieu-at-the-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"A day after she wasaccusedof being a competitor unworthy of respect, China's Qinwen Zheng advanced to the semifinals of the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s singles Olympic tennis event with a 6\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00937, 6\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00934, 7\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00936 win over Germany\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Angelique Kerber.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 228, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 69, \"end\": 74, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9970395720191376, \"rank\": 0.0027174768309664974, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 84, \"end\": 89, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Jie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8282972059932993e-27, \"text\": \"Zheng\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Jie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Jie\"}, {\"begin\": 211, \"end\": 227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angelique_Kerber\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Angelique Kerber\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angelique_Kerber\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angelique_Kerber\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was precisely the kind of spirited comeback win that demands respect.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 301, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But let today\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s discussion be about the defeated player.\", \"from\": 303, \"to\": 361, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For this match\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094that, fittingly, ended in a third-set tiebreaker\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094marks the end of Kerber\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s career, a run as estimable as it is instructive.\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 506, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a swell life being a mid-tier tennis player.\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 559, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s financially lucrative and there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s lots of travel, often exotic.\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 632, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You work for yourself.\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It beats most desk jobs.\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 680, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But for Kerber, it was ultimately unsatisfying.\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 729, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For her first five or six years on tour, she was tracking for a fine career.\", \"from\": 730, \"to\": 806, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A converted lefty, she won her share of matches, even reaching the odd major semifinal.\", \"from\": 807, \"to\": 894, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But when she entered her mid-20s, her ranking had barely entered its mid-20s.\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 972, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, the deluge.\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 991, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kerber changed coaches, got herself into peak shape, retooled her game to maximize her strengths (like speed) and minimize her weaknesses (like her second serve) \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 and the results came fast.\", \"from\": 992, \"to\": 1184, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The same month she turned 28, she claimed her first major title, beating Serena Williams in a three-set final to win the 2016 Australian Open.\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1259, \"end\": 1274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Serena Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At Wimbledon that year, she again reached the final, this time losing to Williams.\", \"from\": 1329, \"to\": 1411, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Less than a month later, she earned silver in women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s singles at the Rio Olympics.\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1496, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Barely a month after that, she closed out her breakthrough year, winning the U.S. Open and becoming the oldest player in WTA history to ascend to the No.1 ranking.\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1618, \"end\": 1621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_Tennis_Association\", \"score\": 0.9979380997597673, \"rank\": 0.0016566423100291, \"text\": \"WTA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_Tennis_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_Tennis_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not that she was done.\", \"from\": 1662, \"to\": 1684, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Winning became a habit.\", \"from\": 1685, \"to\": 1708, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2018, the year she turned 30, she made the semifinals in Australia, the quarterfinals in Paris and then won Wimbledon, again beating Williams.\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1854, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1769, \"end\": 1778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9603186578987234, \"rank\": 0.031991597857207836, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1801, \"end\": 1806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999850051338195, \"rank\": 0.00014997114958852927, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Suddenly, the modest player for the first half of her career was a generational player, one French Open short of the career slam.\", \"from\": 1855, \"to\": 1984, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After a year off for maternity leave, Kerber was still bringing it this season, mixing defense with offense, power with lefty deception.\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 2122, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But then came five straight defeats this summer and her decision to sayfertig.\\u00c2  Kerber leaves the sport with Hall of Fame credentials.\", \"from\": 2123, \"to\": 2258, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She leaves with over $30 million in prize money, one of the 10-highest totals in WTA history.\\u00c2  Above all, she leaves as a figurehead for the idea that your career is what you want it to be.\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2449, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2340, \"end\": 2343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_Tennis_Association\", \"score\": 0.9979380997597673, \"rank\": 0.0016566423100291, \"text\": \"WTA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_Tennis_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_Tennis_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re unsatisfied working in the equivalent of middle management, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s possible to break through a glass ceiling and become the best player in the world.\", \"from\": 2450, \"to\": 2611, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 2613, \"to\": 2639, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Jon Wertheim is a senior writer for Sports Illustrated and has been part of the full-time SI writing staff since 1997, largely focusing on the tennis beat, sports business and social issues, and enterprise journalism.\", \"from\": 2640, \"to\": 2921, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2704, \"end\": 2716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Wertheim\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jon Wertheim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Wertheim\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Wertheim\"}, {\"begin\": 2740, \"end\": 2758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.415025817513861e-18, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to his work at SI, he is a correspondent for \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009c60 Minutes\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d and a commentator for The Tennis Channel.\", \"from\": 2922, \"to\": 3037, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He has authored 11 books and has been honored with two Emmys, numerous writing and investigative journalism awards, and the Eugene Scott Award from the International Tennis Hall of Fame.\", \"from\": 3038, \"to\": 3224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3093, \"end\": 3098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmy_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9999999947508513, \"rank\": 5.249260672722548e-09, \"text\": \"Emmys\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmy_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmy_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 3162, \"end\": 3174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gene_Scott\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.744952300403238e-21, \"text\": \"Eugene Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gene_Scott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gene_Scott\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wertheim is a longtime member of the New York Bar Association (retired), the International Tennis Writers Association and the Writers Guild of America.\", \"from\": 3225, \"to\": 3376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3262, \"end\": 3270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999982264853, \"rank\": 1.7080027488610353e-09, \"text\"